step_data.thought:
Looking at the current page state, I can see that the map is now at zoom level 15 as indicated by the URL 'http://127.0.0.1:3000/#map=15/42.8960/-75.1080'. The image tiles in the accessibility tree confirm this, showing URLs like 'https://tile.openstreetmap.org/15/9547/12053.png'.

At zoom level 15, the map is showing very detailed road information including small streets, paths, building outlines, and road labels. This is a significant increase from the lower zoom levels and should provide the detailed road information that the user requested.

The 'Zoom In' link (bid 406) is still available and focused, which means I could zoom in even further to level 16 if needed. However, at the current zoom level 15, the map is already displaying detailed road information. The user's goal was to 'zoom in on the map to see more detailed road information,' which has been accomplished.

Since we've successfully increased the zoom level multiple times (from what appears to have been level 10 initially to level 15 now), and we can now see detailed road information, I'll send a message to the user indicating that we've completed their request.
